SIMPLE: aniline
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aniline
<hw>An"i*line</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Anil</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An organic base belonging
to the phenylamines. It may be regarded as ammonia in which one hydrogen
atom has been replaced by the radical phenyl. It is a colorless, oily
liquid, originally obtained from indigo by distillation, but now largely
manufactured from coal tar or nitrobenzene as a base from which many
brilliant dyes are made.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aniline</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Aniline
<hw>An"i*line</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Made from, or of the nature of,
aniline.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>anilinism</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>anilism</ent>⟦br⟧
